Class Transactions

  • java.lang.Object
    • operations.Transactions

  • public class Transactions
extends java.lang.Object
    The Transactions class handles all of the transactions between Player objects when they want to trade and during bankruptcy (and saving from bankruptcy)

    Robert Keenan and Ciaran Nolan

      • playerToPlayerTrade

        static void playerToPlayerTrade(Player initiatingPlayer)
        This class handles all of the player to player trading. It calls initiateTrade() from this trade with another player and then proceeds to iterate over both players. It asks the user's what they want to trade first of all such as Jail Free card, Property, Cash or to leave the trade. It will then check whether the user has entered a valid entry such as them not having any jail free cards but still wanting to trade one. It goes through these cases until both players decide they are finished trading all of the items they want to. It will then ask both users to accept the terms of the trade and if they do, it will complete the relevant trades of assets.
        Parameters:
        initiatingPlayer - The Player Object wishing to initiate a trade

      • bankruptcySingleTransaction

        private static void bankruptcySingleTransaction(Player bankruptPlayer,
                                                Player purchasingPlayer,
                                                TitleDeed tradeItem,
                                                java.io.BufferedReader userInput)
        This method is used for a player who is bankrupt and a single transaction is made with another player. THe trade item can be passed in as a TitleDeed card if the trade is with a CanOwn item. It will then ask purchasing player if they want to accept the trade and if they do, the trade will be processed.
        Parameters:
        bankruptPlayer - The player object bankrupt who wants to trade with another
        purchasingPlayer - The purchasing player of an asset from the bankrupt player
        tradeItem - The item to be traded in TitleDeed object form
        userInput - BufferedReader used for simulating user input for much more complex tests in JUnit

      • saveFromBankruptcyTrade

        public static void saveFromBankruptcyTrade(Player bankruptPlayer,
                                           java.io.BufferedReader userInput)
        To the save from bankruptcy in terms of trading, we can use this method to trade cards or properties which checks whether there is a player willing to make a trade with the bankrupt player. If there are only 2 oeople in the playerList, then the single transaction is enacted between them. Otherwise, if there are no other players who wish to trade then it goes to auction
        Parameters:
        bankruptPlayer - The player object who is bankrupt and wishes to trade to gain money
        userInput - BufferedReader used for simulating user input for much more complex tests in JUnit
